          - "db_password exists"
          - "mq_password exists"
      no_log: true

This creates:

was_password: <retrieved password>
db_password: <retrieved password>
mq_password: <retrieved password>
Notes

The role uses the same client certificate and key from roles/cyberark_ccp_password/files/ for all lookups in that role invocation. The CyberArk module expects path-based client_cert and client_key, and the password returned by CCP is exposed in Content.

